      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOVIE NIGHT (1) missed the kick so had to go back last start then unleashed over the final stages to just miss a dramatic win first-up over this distance at Kembla. Back in fine fettle and if she sorts her barrier manners out this should be a breakthrough win for the nicely bred filly. WEE WINN (7) ran a nice race first-up over 1300m at Kembla then wasn't comfortable on a bog track at Hawkesbury last time. Finds the right conditions to bounce back to form. ROYAL BOTANIC (6) continues to progress well through her maiden campaign. Led but just failed to hang on most recently over 1300m at Scone. Will give them something to catch. HONEYSUCKLE (10) was 38 days between runs when midfield over this trip at Kembla last start. Has only raced twice so there is plenty of scope for improvement.",
